OL,5,CFREEDOM FOR RAMBLERS TO ROAM?          
OL,7,G"For more than 100 years, ramblers have
OL,8,Gbeen campaigning for freedom to roam   
OL,9,Gopen land with responsibility," says   
OL,10,CNicky WardenGfromCThe Ramblers'        
OL,11,CAssociation.                           
OL,12,G                                       
OL,13,G"That isCmoor, heath, down and mountain
OL,14,Gland ` land which has not been spoilt  
OL,15,Gby development.                        
OL,16,G                                       
OL,17,G"At present, if ramblers want to roam, 
OL,18,Gthey have to getCpermission from the   
OL,19,Cland-owner,Gwhich is extremely rare."  
